### API Design
- Follow RESTful conventions for HTTP APIs
- Use consistent error response formats
- Version APIs when introducing breaking changes
- Validate all input at the API boundary

### Testing
- Write tests for all new features and bug fixes
- Maintain minimum 80% code coverage for critical paths
- Use descriptive test names that explain the expected behaviour
- Mock external dependencies in unit tests
- Use factories or fixtures for test data

### Security
- Never commit secrets, API keys, or credentials
- Use environment variables for configuration
- Validate and sanitise all user input
- Follow the principle of least privilege for permissions

### Performance
- Optimise database queries — avoid N+1 patterns
- Use pagination for list endpoints
- Cache expensive computations where appropriate
- Profile before optimising — measure, don't guess

### Accessibility
- Follow WCAG 2.1 AA guidelines for frontend work
- Use semantic HTML elements
- Ensure keyboard navigation works correctly
